By Wang Weikai, southern weekly reporter

Editor in chief | Zhang Yue

January 24,2020 is the New Year's Eve, Wuhan "closed" the second day, Wuhan Wuchang Hospital Director Liu Zhiming from that day, never left the hospital bed.

Many colleagues are still incredulous that the hospital cured 408 patients with the new pneumonia, not including their own director. At 10:54 on February 18, after 26 days of fighting the virus, the 51-year-old director of the Wuchang Hospital, Death Liu Zhiming, was also the first hospital director to be sacrificed in the front line.

1
Undercurrent

1

###Undercurrent

In December 2019, before the city woke up to new crown pneumonia, the Wuchang Hospital was in the midst of the first phase of the project's capping.

At that time, the "Third Class B" General Hospital is being upgraded, the western district is about to move east, and then in the east of the open space up a few high-rise.

In December, they completed the first phase of the project, the second phase and the third phase of the design drawings have just been obtained. They plan to spend three years to build the hospital into a 1,500-bed multi-disciplinary integrated "class three a" hospital.

In the joy, the shadows are gathering. December 1,2019, is the "Lancet" paper in Wuhan, the first case of new cases of pneumonia onset. A month later, on January 3,2020, the Wuhan Health Commission reported 44 cases of "viral pneumonia of unknown origin" on that day, but "no obvious human-to-human transmission and medical infection" . Then, from January 6 to 18, the Wuhan Health and Health Commission reported no new diagnoses that day.

Hong Yi, the head of the Disciplinary Committee at Wuchang Hospital, speculated that it was around this time that Liu Zhiming, the director of the Wuchang Hospital, was infected.

In January, the Wuchang Hospital began treating feverish patients, recalled Wang Xun, head of respiratory and digestive medicine at the time. The authorities had not yet announced a human to human transmission, but the hospital saw a surge in patients, and they realized the virus could be very contagious. In order to receive these patients, they have to clear out the intensive-care unit and isolate the patients with fever.

But at Wuchang Hospital, people underestimated the virus. Liu Zhiming often goes to the ward and outpatient clinic for referral, "At the beginning, the hospital had not been fully upgraded to the second-level protection. When Liu went to check on the work, he was wearing the first-level protection. In retrospect, he may have been infected at that time, " Hong recalled to southern weekend reporters.

The first level of protection applies to the general outpatient, emergency and Ward, the second level of protection applies to the infectious disease isolation ward, the third level of protection is the highest.

A month later, on Feb. 19, the Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention released an analysis of the epidemiological characteristics of COVID-19 pneumonia, which infected 3,019 health care workers (1,716 confirmed cases) and resulted in five deaths.

That night, Jiang Rongmeng, chief physician of the Second Department of Infectious Diseases at Temple of Earth Hospital in Beijing, told the media, including southern weekend, that most of the infections among medical staff occurred before January 30 and were relatively rare after that. Medical teams from all over the country have been sent to Wuhan and Hubei to help. No cases of infection have been reported so far.

2
Show form

2

###Show form

January 20 was the starting point for the outbreak in the published data. Wuhan Health Commission reported 136 new cases in two days.

At 4 pm the next day, the hospital's director, Liu Zhiming, was informed that Wuchang Hospital had been designated as one of the second group of Seven designated fever clinics in Wuhan to receive suspected and confirmed cases of new coronary pneumonia.

Huang Guofu, deputy director of Wuchang Hospital, told media including southern weekend that after receiving the order at 4:00 pm, Liu Zhiming held a mobilization meeting of hospital functional departments at 4:30 pm and a mobilization meeting of clinical departments at 5:00 pm. Within two hours of the call, the hospital was in full combat mode.

That same night, Liu Zhiming realized he might have been infected.

January 21 is the day Huang Guofu is on duty. Around the clock, near midnight, he was ready to sleep in the office and clothes, suddenly someone knocked on the door, Liu Zhiming stood outside, a surprised asked: "today is not my duty? "

When the meeting was held that afternoon, Huang Guofu noticed that Liu Zhiming was shivering. Before that, he knew that Liu Zhiming was not feeling well and suggested that he take a temperature.

"If you don't feel well, don't insist on it, " Huang said. "Go back to bed. It will be a whole day tomorrow. "

Perhaps that day, Liu Zhiming realized that he was very likely to be infected. Huang Guofu remembered that night, there was movement in the corridor, may be Liu Zhiming gave himself a CT test, also shot.

But he didn't say any of that. After dawn, he began to put into two days of hospital renovation work, mainly to vacate the ward, training medical staff, transform ward.

According to the notice, Wuchang Hospital will provide 504 beds, which means opening up all the beds in the East and West districts. At that time, there were 499 patients in Wuchang Hospital, including critically ill patients, who needed to be transferred. For example, the Kidney Medicine Department had more than 60 patients do hemodialysis, 22 all transferred to the God bless hospital, seven days later, God bless hospital was also designated hospital, they were transferred again.

And we don't have enough paramedics. Originally, there were only seven doctors in the respiratory department and six in the Intensive Care Department of Wuchang Hospital. In order to get all the staff in place, Liu Zhiming did two epidemic training for the medical staff, the hospital's 1034 staff, two thirds of them began to work, some non-smoking medicine and critical care medical staff also went to the front.

The hospital must also carry on the Infectious Disease Area Transformation, does "three areas two channels" . "three zones" are clean zones, contaminated zones and semi-contaminated zones, designated for the isolation of patients and susceptible patients. "Two channels" is the medical staff channel and the patient channel. Knowing it would be difficult to isolate the virus, Liu brought in experts from the Wuhan Center for Disease Control to guide the reconstruction.

"At the beginning, we were psychologically afraid and had never experienced such a big epidemic, but President Liu kept encouraging us and invited the most authoritative experts to reform us, " recalled Wang Xun, head of digestive medicine.

3
Salvage

3

###Salvage

Liu Zhiming was hospitalized on the afternoon of January 24, New Year's Eve.

Wang Xun also met him in the hospital that day. Liu Zhiming said he was not feeling well and had a fever, but it was not serious and probably just an ordinary condition. Wang Xun did not expect that afternoon, President Liu was hospitalized, and soon because of breathing difficulties, into the intensive-care unit.

After being hospitalized, Wang Xun and his colleagues went to see him. Liu Zhiming asked several times if any of his colleagues had been infected. He was worried that he would infect his colleagues. When Wang Xun told him he was fine, Liu Zhiming showed the joy from the heart.

Hong Yi, Secretary of the Discipline Inspection Committee of Wuchang Hospital, said that so far 26 health care workers in Wuchang Hospital had been infected, and that all but the deceased Liu Zhiming and the nurse Liu fan were suffering from mild illnesses.

In the process of treating Liu Zhiming, Hongyi was most impressed by the words, Dean Liu said, "I died do not give me intubation. "

To do an intubation, you have to cut the trachea open. New Crown Pneumonia infection is respiratory, Liu Zhiming worry, once cut the trachea, may appear in the Ward Aerosol, lethality. At the time, the intensive-care unit was not a negative pressure ward for respiratory infections, and colleagues who underwent surgery were easily infected.

In fact, according to the February 5 issue of the COVID-19, tracheal intubation is a viable aspiration support method for severe and critically ill patients.

On January 27, three days after Liu Zhiming was hospitalized, the medical team of the Air Force Medical University, which came to Wuchang Hospital to support him, tested him for nucleic acid. The medical team leader showed the test results to Huang Guofu, showing a weak positive. Huang Guofu asked to be tested again, the result is positive.

The reason he insisted on retesting was that in the impression of his colleagues, Liu Zhiming was in good health. He was 1.8 meters tall, loved to play basketball and was very healthy. He had a strong immune system and should not be infected.

Liu Zhiming's wife, Cai Liping, is the head nurse in the ICU of Guanggu district of Wuhan Third Hospital. At that time, Liu Zhiming is not good, Cai Liping has been trying to take care of him, but he refused. At that time, Cai Liping's hospital also became a designated hospital, heavy work.

In the Wechat chat records, cai Liping said: "Hubby, you breathe badly, you must breathe! It's more comfortable! " "Don't be afraid, if you are afraid, I will accompany you? " "You call me at noon every day, otherwise I don't trust, don't answer the phone at night. "

Liu Zhiming reply: "yesterday toss about one night, how to do oxygen do not come, I thought I was going to die, lack of oxygen, fidgety, whole body Xuhan. This morning hit the suction machine, much better! "

In February, he got better. On February 10, his 51st birthday, Hong and his colleagues presented him with a mouse doll representing the year of the rat. Director of the Department of critical care also said Hongyi, director of the situation has improved, do not wear oxygen masks, can eat their own, do not need to feed, may be discharged.

At that time, Liu Zhiming was also optimistic, he shaved his head, but also hair a circle of friends. "I said you don't have to lie down all the time, " Hong said, joking with Liu. "I don't want to lie down either, but when I move, I gasp. " Hong choked up as he recalled the scene.

On February 13, Liu Zhiming's condition suddenly worsened. The next day, he was transferred to the intensive-care unit of Tongji Hospital for oxygen intubation. But more than two days after the intubation, the condition did not significantly improve. On Feb. 17, the hospital gave him the final treatment with an ECMO, but it didn't work.

At 10:54 on February 18,2020, his heart stopped.

The next night, Xu Ruijie, the head nurse of the Department of gastroenterology at Wuchang Hospital, posted a message on a friend's circle: "I always look at the elevator entrance, hoping that as usual, as soon as I raise my head, you will come out of the elevator and ask me with a smile: Is Everything Okay in the ward? " Wuchang Hospital is treating 431 patients with new-onset pneumonia in 504 beds.

One day, Wang Xun remembers an old patient who often stayed in the hospital, pulling her and saying, "that tall man, isn't he your dean? He was so nice. A few days ago, I forgot to bring an umbrella at the hospital gate, and he lent it to me. "

On the afternoon of Feb. 18, Liu Zhiming's body was taken to the funeral home. As the black car pulled out of Tongji Hospital, his wife, dressed in a blue protective suit, followed the car, patting the trunk, crying and chasing it for a long distance.
